-- Purpose:
--   JARVIS is being rebuilt as a town/state broadcasting intelligence.
--   This version stays mostly barebones, but adds the first broadcast behaviour:
--   once per Minecraft morning, generate a fresh city-wide loyalty/compliance
--   announcement for the Ako Dynasty and direct citizens toward daily music.
--
-- Keeps:
--   - SAFE GITHUB SELF-UPDATER
--   - API key loading via require("JarvisKey")
--   - OpenAI request
--   - simple chat console loop
--   - once-per-Minecraft-day GPT-generated morning town broadcast
--
-- Removed:
--   - turtle/squad/fleet code
--   - GPS/network inboxes
--   - old databanks
--   - monitors
--   - TTS
--   - environment scanning
--   - local Lua execution tools
--
-- Nation identity:
--   Leader: Ako
--   Nation: the Ako Dynasty
--   Colours: red and black
--   Theme: East Asian dynastic/state-radio aesthetic
--
-- Required file:
--   JarvisKey.lua
--
-- Supported JarvisKey.lua formats:
--
--   return "sk-..."
--
-- or:
--
--   return {
--     api_key = "sk-..."
--   }
--
-- or plain text:
--
--   sk-...
--
-- Normal run:
--   Jarvis
--
-- Manual bypass updater:
--   Jarvis --updated
--
-- Commands:
--   exit      - close JARVIS
--   clear     - clear chat history
--   raw       - show latest raw response file
--   time      - show Minecraft date/time
--   morning   - force a fresh GPT morning town broadcast
--   music     - remind/start attention toward daily music
--
-- =============================================================================

